corr =df.corr()
sns.heatmap(corr, vmin=-1, annot=True)
# correlation heatmap is showing a high correlation to Emails per day and Calls per day in realtion to Recruits per Month.
#The highest correlation on this map is the correlation of Recruitment Bonus to Recruits per Month at .856
#The lowest correlation which should prob. not be a considerd factor would be Age of the recruiter at a -0.073.
#histogram of distribution of Reruits per Month shows highest distribution around 6 Recruits.

location = "downloads/CollegeRecruitingData1.xlsx"
df2 = pd.read_excel(location)
df2.rename(columns={'Recruits per Month': 'RPM',"Emails per Day":'EPD','Calls per Day':'CPD','Recruitment Bonus':'RB'}, inplace = True)

import statsmodels.formula.api as smf
reg = smf.ols('RPM ~ CPD + EPD+ RB', data=df2).fit()
reg.summary()
#this linear regression would only work at columns labeled one word..

OLS INTERPRETATION 
*the coefficient tells you how much the dependent variable is expected to increase (if the coefficient is positive) or decrease (if the coefficient is negative) when that independent variable increases by one. Positive increase to Recruits per month when, Calls Per Day- Emails Per Day- Recruit Bonus is increased by one.
*Low P value showing that I have added meaningful additions to model. Significant 
* Adjusted R-Square is showing a good fit, from 0-1 this one is at .913
